Use these signals to trade smarter with Robinhood or any broker. Our newsletter is your edge in the market. What are Bollinger Bands? Bollinger Bands are a technical analysis tool that helps traders identify volatility and potential price reversals. They consist of a moving average (the "middle band") and two standard deviation lines (the "upper" and "lower" bands) that expand and contract based on market volatility.
  • When price touches the upper band, the asset may be overbought.
  • When price touches the lower band, the asset may be oversold.
  • Bands widen during high volatility and contract during low volatility.
 Why Bollinger Bands Matter Bollinger Bands help you:
  • Spot trend reversals and breakouts
  • Identify periods of high and low volatility
  • Time your entries and exits with greater confidence
